The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, January 06, 2004 				 Fireworks raid ends in arrests
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The police seized a huge cache of banned fireworks and ingredients to make crackers during extensive raids in central and north Calcutta on Monday. Two persons were arrested.																								The first raid was carried out at Baithakkhana market, in the Amherst Street police station area. We rounded up Pradip Saha from his godown and seized 600 kg of cracker ingredients, said P. Ravi, deputy commissioner of police (north). 																								Sahas interrogation led the cops to Chitpur, where a godown yielded 400 kg of ingredients in gunny bags. There, Raju Saha was arrested. The material was to be supplied to cracker units in South 24-Parganas and Howrah.
